The evidence with the title 'Financial Services Industry spotlight | selectusa.gov ' says In 2016, finance and insurance represented 7.3 percent (or $1.4 trillion) of U.S. gross domestic product .  ... In 2015 , at least 130 of Fortune's Global 500 companies have chosen to locate their headquarters in the United States to take advantage of its creative , competitive , and comprehensive financial services sector . 
